children.name: print a2
children.definition: print to produce words, numbers, or pictures on paper, using a machine which puts ink onto the surface : in
examples: i need to make a few changes before i print the document.
the company’s name was printed in bold letters across the top of the page.
a printed letter
the printer’s switched on but it won’t print.
as a newspaper publisher he understood the power ofthe printed word(= words that are printed on paper ).
the leaflets will be printedonrecycled paper.
i'm waiting for a document to print.

children.name: print c2
children.definition: print writing that has been printed, for example in books or newspapers : bản in (thay vì bản viết tay)
examples: there was no print at all on the backs of the tickets.
in print(= printed in a book, newspaper etc )
it must be really exciting to see your work in print.
the pleasure of seeing my name in print
into print
very little of his poetry actuallygot into print(= was printed).
the book was rushedintoprint as quickly as possible.
print[u] c2 the letters in which sth is printed : chữ in
the print quality of the new printer is excellent.
in bold/ small/ large print
the title is in bold print.
the book is also available inlarge print.
this novel is available in large print for readers with poor eyesight.

children.name: print b2
children.definition: print to include a piece of writing in a newspaper or magazine
examples: some newspapers still refuse to print certain swear words.
they printed his letter in tuesday's paper.
i wrote to the newspaper but my letter wasn’t printed.
‘the express’ was the first paper to print the story.
‘the telegraph’ has printed numerous articles on this subject over the last three years.

children.name: edition b2
children.definition: editiona particular form or version of a published text: ấn bản
examples: a hardback/paperback edition
the paperback edition costs £7.99.
thepaperback/hardbackedition of the dictionary
the regional editions of the paper contain specific information for that area.
the us edition of marie claire magazine

children.name: edition x
children.definition: edition a particular version of a text maintained by regular revision : ấn bản
examples: the textbook was first published in 1858 and is now in its 39th edition.
a first/second/third etc editionthe first edition was published in 1986.
a new editionthe new edition of the dictionary includes a cd-rom.
a revised edition(= one that has more information than a previous edition, or contains corrections)the revised edition includes a chapter on gordon brown.
a limited/special edition(= a small number of special copies produced at one time only )they have produced a new limited edition cd.
she's got some very valuable limited editions on her shelves.
produce/bring out an edition(= of a book, newspaper, or other product )this special edition of the vw beetle was produced in the 1970s.
publish an edition(= of a book or newspaper )the first edition of the book was published in 1982.

children.name: publication b2
children.definition: publication the process of printing a book, magazine etc and offering it for sale: xuất bản
examples: when is the publicationdate(= when will the book be available to buy) ?
the brochure will be ready for publication in september.
publication of
will you arrange the publicationofthe names of the winners?
she was in england for the publication of her new book.
for publication(= intended to be published)
he spent his holiday writing reviews for publication.
a lot of work goes on behind the scenes to prepare a book like this for publication

children.name: publication b2
children.definition: publication a book, magazine, newspaper or document in which information or stories are published : xuất bản phẩm
examples: our latest publication is a magazine for health enthusiasts.
he was the author of 70 major scientific publications.
a weekly publication

children.name: printing x
children.definition: printing the activity or business of producing writing or images on paper or other material with a machine : in ấn
examples: the invention of printing
the printing industry
a printing error
she runs her own printing business.

children.name: publishing x
children.definition: publishing the business of producing books and magazines : ngành xuất bản
examples: tony wants to get a job in publishing.
a newpublishing house(= publishing company)
how long have you worked in publishing?
electronic publishing is a rapidly expanding field.

children.name: unpublished x
children.definition: unpublished written but not yet published : chưa xuất bản
examples: after his death, his daughter found an unpublished manuscript among his papers.
a collection of unpublished poems

children.name: bring out b2
children.definition: bring out to produce a new book:phát hành
examples: fay weldon has just brought out a new collection of stories.
scribner will bring out a memoir by candace gringritch in the autumn.
he phoned to say they want to bring out a second edition.

children.name: publish b1
children.definition: publish xuất bản, phát hành
examples: 1to arrange for a book, magazine etc to be written, printed, and sold :
the first edition was published in 1765.
they are publishing the dictionary on cd-rom.
‘moby dick’ was first published in london in 1851.
‘i’ve had a remarkable life,’ says the 60-year-old author, who has published 35 books.
king has made history by publishing a novel on the world wide web.
2if a newspaper or magazine publishes a letter, article etc, it prints it for people to read:
we love reading your letters and we try to publish as many as possible.

children.name: to print in a larger size
blow up x
children.definition: blow upto print a photograph or picture in a larger size : in phóng to
examples: a photograph of them is blown up to fill two full pages.
this section of the print has been blown up so that the enemy’s tanks can be clearly seen.
you should blow that picture up and frame it.

children.name: enlarge x
children.definition: enlarge to print a bigger copy of a photograph or document.enlargeis more formal thanblowup: in phóng to
examples: that’s a nice photo, why don’t you get it enlarged?
if the opening is too small, you can always enlarge it later.
the new photocopier will enlarge documents by up to 100%.
editing software that enables you to enlarge and crop photographs
when the photograph was enlarged, it was possible to read the writing on the envelope.
enlargement[c] a larger version of a photo that has been printed:bảnphóng to
an enlargement of the wedding photo
enlarger[c] a piece of equipment used especially by photographers to make pictures or photographs bigger máy phóng ảnh to

children.name: printer x
children.definition: printer a person whose job is to print books, newspapers and magazines : thợ in

children.name: stamp b2
children.definition: stamp to put a pattern, sign, or letters on something, using a special tool : đóng dấu
examples: the woman at the desk stamped my passport.
among the papers was a brown folder stamped ‘secret’.
it is necessary to stamp your passport.
stamp sth on sth
stamp the date on all the letters.
stamp sth with sth
every carton of yoghurt is stampedwitha sell-by date.

children.name: reissue x
children.definition: reissue to produce a record, book etc again, after it has not been available for some time:
examples: an early jazz record reissued on cd.
the recording has been reissued to celebrate the conductor's 80th birthday.
reissue[c]

children.name: printing x
children.definition: printinga single impression of a book :
examples: the second printing was ready just after christmas
the first printing of her book was 10,000 copies.

children.name: impression x
children.definition: impression uk a particular printed version of a book, especially one reprinted from existing type, plates, or film with no or only minor alteration:
examples: this is the second impression of the encyclopedia.
a copy of the first impression

children.name: print run x
children.definition: print run the number of books or magazines that are printed at the same time
examples: bambang said the magazine is expected to reach a print run of 20,000 copies within the next few months.

children.name: printing press x
children.definition: printing press a machine that prints books, newspapers or magazines : máy in (số lượng lớn)

children.name: to print sth in large quantities
print out x
children.definition: print/print out to produce a printed copy of a computer document :
examples: my printer prints out at 8 pages per minute.
she printed three copies of the letter.
could you print a copy off for me?
i’ll print the file out and then we can look at it.

children.name: reprint x
children.definition: reprint to print a book, story, newspaper article etc again : in lại, tái bản
examples: the first edition sold out so we are reprinting it/it is reprinting.
reprint[c]
1an occasion when more copies of a book are printed because all the copies of it have been sold: tái xuất bản
2a book that is printed again : tái bản

children.name: print b2
children.definition: print to produce a newspaper, magazine or book in large quantities: in (xuất bản)
examples: over five million copies of the paper are printed every day.
when the book was first written no publisher would print it.
20 000 copies of the novel will be printed in hardback.

children.name: in print c2
children.definition: in/ out of printif a book is in print,new copies of it are still being printed, and if it is out of print,it is no longer being printed and you cannot buy new copies : còn in/ ngừng in
examples: is her work still in print?
after fifty years, the book is still in print.
classic literature nevergoesout of print.
